===Adjective===
'''red''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''redder''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''reddest''')

#Having red as its [[colour]].
#Leftwing, socialist or Communist (''Red China'', the People's Republic of China; ''red scare'', an instance of paranoia about Communism; 'red menace', (formerly) the real or supposed threat from the Soviet Union; ''reds under the bed'', the supposed presence of Communist or Soviet-sympathizing spies or fellow-travellers; ''red-baiting'', persecution of suspected Communists; ''red Clydeside'', (formerly) a popular name for the Clydeside region of Scotland, whose population had strong socialist sympathies; ''red Ken'', pet-name for Ken Livingstone, socialist mayor of London; ''red Vienna'', popular name for 1920s Vienna, which had a socialist city government; ''red-green coalition'', term used in Europe to refer to a coalition between a socialist or social democratic party and a Green party).
#(In the modern United States) Supportive of the Republican Party (''red states'', states which voted for the Republican presidential candidate).

